Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.93,0:00:22.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If doing that means no one will cry, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.17,0:01:59.53,Title,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(278,537)}#19  Idealism's End (The Answer)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.68,0:02:23.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You certainly took your time \Ngetting here, Emiya Shirou.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.08,0:02:26.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it finally occurred to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.88,0:02:30.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There can't be two of those pendants.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.01,0:02:30.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was originally—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.98,0:02:31.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.94,0:02:39.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After your life was saved, you carried \Nit for the rest of your days.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.07,0:02:43.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A bequest of Tohsaka Rin's father, \Nunique in all the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.29,0:02:47.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When summoning a Heroic Spirit, \Na catalyst is needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.62,0:02:51.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But Tohsaka Rin did not have one for the invocation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.60,0:02:52.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.75,0:02:56.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,she assumed she'd summoned a Servant at random.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.55,0:03:01.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But no Heroic Spirit is summoned by chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.34,0:03:05.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A link is always required between summoner and spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.18,0:03:08.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If Rin had no catalyst, that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.64,0:03:09.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.73,0:03:15.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The summoned Heroic Spirit, not the \Nsummoner, possessed the catalyst.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.94,0:03:19.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The concept of time does not exist where \Nthe Heroic Spirits are recorded.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.82,0:03:23.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Heroic Spirits from the past are treated \Nidentically to those of the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.05,0:03:25.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In short...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.66,0:03:26.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.97,0:03:32.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It means that it's possible to summon \Nsomeone who exists in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.85,0:03:33.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.38,0:03:35.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Tohsaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.98,0:03:38.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I handed her over to Matou Shinji \Nwhen he stopped by earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.78,0:03:40.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You what?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.13,0:03:41.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Relax, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.64,0:03:45.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Leave the little lady to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.19,0:03:46.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lancer?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.72,0:03:49.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have my Master's orders, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.27,0:03:53.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Keeping her alive has always been \Nmy reason for working with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.11,0:03:57.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, it's been really nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.28,0:04:01.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For me, it's rare to enjoy a task I've been given.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.65,0:04:04.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So until this is over, let me look after her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.47,0:04:07.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After that, we'll be enemies again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.62,0:04:14.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Take care of Tohsaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.25,0:04:15.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.32,0:04:22.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I shall remain here, Lancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.73,0:04:24.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.18,0:04:26.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your Master is the little lady now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.91,0:04:28.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I understand that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.43,0:04:32.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I must bear witness to this battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.23,0:04:36.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Really now?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.52,0:04:37.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Have it your way, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.44,0:04:42.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"Bear witness," huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.82,0:04:44.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.07,0:04:50.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you interfered now, severing my pact with \NRin would have been for nothing, Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.33,0:04:52.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.15,0:04:55.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come what may, I shan't interfere \Nwith your battle with Shirou.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.29,0:04:58.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But in return, I want you to answer one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.99,0:05:01.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you so intent on killing Shirou?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.17,0:05:04.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you even ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.51,0:05:10.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just as he can't accept me, \NI can't accept him. That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.00,0:05:11.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That cannot be true!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.66,0:05:16.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You should embody Emiya Shirou's \Nideals in Heroic Spirit form.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.90,0:05:19.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why would that ideal reject itself?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.53,0:05:25.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike you, I didn't become a Heroic \NSpirit entirely on my own merits.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.86,0:05:28.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I became one by selling my posthumous self.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.85,0:05:30.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm nothing but a Guardian.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.33,0:05:32.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A Guardian?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.58,0:05:36.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Off you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.86,0:05:46.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's with the stink eye?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.93,0:05:50.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You still can't read a situation, can you, Tohsaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.89,0:05:53.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you see the position you're in?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.10,0:05:56.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Try looking in a mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.19,0:05:58.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'd say you're the clueless one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.86,0:06:00.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, drop the tough act.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.77,0:06:02.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.09,0:06:05.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unbelievable...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.64,0:06:07.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like nothing I say will get through to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.16,0:06:11.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good! That's more like it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.20,0:06:15.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you've finally figured out you belong to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.33,0:06:20.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Man, I love legs that have just enough muscle...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.73,0:06:24.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It'll make tormenting you all the more fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.14,0:06:25.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.10,0:06:36.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about that, punk.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.81,0:06:39.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My fist went flying before my words.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.77,0:06:42.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lancer?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.19,0:06:44.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.15,0:06:46.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.86,0:06:47.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Save it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.88,0:06:50.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have those bonds cut in a jiffy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.01,0:06:51.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After that, do as you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.91,0:06:54.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Go to the hall and stop those idiots from fighting,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.87,0:06:56.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,or slip out the back and go home. Your call.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.58,0:06:58.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lancer, behind you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.79,0:07:00.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.38,0:07:03.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's quite enough, Lancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.96,0:07:07.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I said to work with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.97,0:07:12.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I never said to get emotionally invested.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.39,0:07:14.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Kirei?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.20,0:07:16.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A Guardian?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.14,0:07:19.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that, after their deaths,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.75,0:07:22.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Guardians become a Counter Force \Nto protect humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.48,0:07:24.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if your circumstances differ,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.36,0:07:26.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you are a Heroic Spirit, regardless.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.57,0:07:28.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's where you're mistaken, Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.95,0:07:31.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Guardians don't protect humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.74,0:07:33.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They're simply cleaners.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.37,0:07:35.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.59,0:07:37.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.14,0:07:39.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I did become a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.70,0:07:42.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just as the man called Emiya Shirou always wished,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.20,0:07:45.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I became a true hero of justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.31,0:07:51.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A hero of justice...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.45,0:07:57.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And that is exactly why I know \Nthat that reality is a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.59,0:08:01.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That that man's life had absolutely no value.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.71,0:08:03.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No value?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.89,0:08:05.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,None.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.08,0:08:07.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Surely you understand, Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.14,0:08:12.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You, who wants to change the past, to take \Nback her decisions, more than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.96,0:08:14.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Saber?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.51,0:08:15.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.60,0:08:19.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You never asked her what her wish was?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.74,0:08:22.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why she desires the Holy Grail \Nenough to commit herself
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.78,0:08:24.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to this pointless bloodbath?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.69,0:08:29.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then allow me to tell you. She is—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.62,0:08:30.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.23,0:08:35.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shirou...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.78,0:08:43.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to use the Holy Grail, \Nthe all-powerful wish granter,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.87,0:08:47.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to undo a decision I once made.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.81,0:09:08.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To undo my mistake...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.60,0:09:12.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To alter the fated destruction of Britain...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.94,0:09:15.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I could not allow myself to die yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.82,0:09:20.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is I why I want to win the Grail.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.07,0:09:25.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I did not live up to my ideals.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.86,0:09:28.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I should never have become king.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.87,0:09:31.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But you are different.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.02,0:09:35.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you not the ideals of Emiya Shirou fully realized?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.80,0:09:38.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The realized ideals, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.38,0:09:45.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that I did become \Nmy own ideal hero of justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.72,0:09:49.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But as a result, I gained nothing but regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.17,0:09:53.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,While alive, I made a pact with the Counter Force.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.58,0:09:55.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After death, having become a Guardian,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.46,0:09:58.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I acted as humanity's Counter Force,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.63,0:10:01.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,fighting those who disrupted the world's balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.20,0:10:04.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Obeying my orders,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.99,0:10:06.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.62,0:10:07.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.54,0:10:10.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And just kept killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.42,0:10:15.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I killed so many, I ceased to care.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.00,0:10:19.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For every life I took, I saved thousands.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.38,0:10:26.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I fought again and again, \Nwhenever I was called upon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.35,0:10:32.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.02,0:10:35.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.73,0:10:37.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And again...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.23,0:10:41.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But there was no end to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.91,0:10:43.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It never ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.91,0:10:48.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't as if I dreamed of a world free of fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.08,0:10:56.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I just didn't want anyone\Nto cry in the world I knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.67,0:11:00.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's when it finally hit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.13,0:11:05.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The ideal that Shirou Emiya embraced \Nwas only a shallow idealism.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.09,0:11:07.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.56,0:11:11.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible to save everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.48,0:11:18.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Saving the many means leaving the few to perish.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.14,0:11:21.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You should know something about that, Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.94,0:11:26.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Those who were bound to fall \Nfrom the seat of happiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.26,0:11:28.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I quickly cut down with my own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.10,0:11:34.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is the proper course of action for a Heroic \NSpirit, for that man's ideal hero of justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.29,0:11:39.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Saving as many as possible is what \Na hero of justice does, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.69,0:11:43.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so, still wishing for no one to die,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.40,0:11:46.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I would have one person die for the sake of many.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.48,0:11:49.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even as I said that I couldn't let anyone be sad,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.73,0:11:54.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I ultimately drove more than a few to despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.48,0:12:00.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is my true identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.58,0:12:03.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of the Heroic Spirit Emiya.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.53,0:12:08.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think if such a man died, \Nthe world would be better for it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.46,0:12:24.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Kill yourself, Emiya Shirou.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.76,0:12:27.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ow...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.78,0:12:32.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't it my Master's credo to never reveal himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.61,0:12:34.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have no such policy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.52,0:12:39.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, you are the one disobeying orders, Lancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.65,0:12:42.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I seem to recall ordering you to terminate Archer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.98,0:12:46.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He'll do himself in without any help from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.92,0:12:49.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, did you put that kid up to this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.99,0:12:52.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing so sinister.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.43,0:12:54.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We have an arrangement.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.93,0:12:59.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We've reached a mutual accord for \Nthe sake of winning the Grail.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.42,0:13:00.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Figures.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.98,0:13:04.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I knew you wouldn't die so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.35,0:13:08.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the point of winning a harmless \Nloser like Shinji to your side?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.40,0:13:11.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You take him for harmless, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.44,0:13:15.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even in this situation, you remain \NTohsaka Rin to the core.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.36,0:13:21.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you were a less capable pupil, \Nthis would be less regrettable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.56,0:13:23.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on, Kotomine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.54,0:13:28.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Was that talk about wanting \Nto save your pupil a lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.07,0:13:31.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing of the sort.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.62,0:13:35.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She is an important pawn that I have \Ntaken great pains to nurture.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.55,0:13:38.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've deceived her these ten long years,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.48,0:13:41.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so what fun would it be if \Nshe left the battle so easily?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.18,0:13:45.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That was why I entrusted her safety to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.84,0:13:48.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You fraud of a priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.44,0:13:51.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Participating in a game that\Nyou're also the referee of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.48,0:13:52.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,is so unfair, it's not even funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.30,0:13:56.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And yet you don't seem all that surprised, Rin.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.95,0:13:59.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then you suspected me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.40,0:14:01.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.23,0:14:05.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Admittedly, it never occurred to me \Nthat I'd been tricked from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.83,0:14:07.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,From the beginning?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.88,0:14:09.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.34,0:14:12.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, when you said, "From the beginning,"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.17,0:14:15.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was wondering how far back that was.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.16,0:14:18.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Kirei, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.79,0:14:22.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Since after this Holy Grail War began?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.68,0:14:25.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or does the "beginning" you speak of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.69,0:14:29.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,refer to the previous Holy Grail War?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.39,0:14:36.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.99,0:14:40.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You were the one who killed my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.23,0:14:42.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.12,0:14:43.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After all, he was my beloved teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.66,0:14:47.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Catching him by surprise was child's play.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.44,0:14:51.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.75,0:14:54.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you know what you are, why hesitate?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.62,0:14:55.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.88,0:14:58.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you have not gone against your ideals.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.43,0:15:00.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did you not simply lose your way
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.32,0:15:02.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,when the very ideals you protected betrayed you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.26,0:15:04.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Were that not the case,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.68,0:15:08.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you would not consider killing yourself \Natonement for your sins.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.88,0:15:16.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this is rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.28,0:15:18.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Atone for my sins?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.22,0:15:21.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be a fool, Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.14,0:15:26.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're right, I was betrayed and \Ndeceived countless times.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.83,0:15:29.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You can't expect anyone to understand a man
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.96,0:15:32.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,willing to lay down his life for others.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.86,0:15:34.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In the end,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.17,0:15:37.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was set up as the mastermind behind \Na conflict and sent to the gallows.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.34,0:15:40.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You must be lying, Archer...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.87,0:15:42.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That was how you died?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.41,0:15:49.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I had any sins, surely I fully atoned \Nfor them in that moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.63,0:15:53.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's not as if I ever wanted gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.43,0:15:56.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I never wanted to be celebrated as a hero, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.66,0:16:00.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I simply wanted an outcome \Nwhere everyone was happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.91,0:16:03.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But that was never given to me, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.35,0:16:05.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Neither in life, nor afterward.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.87,0:16:10.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I knew that Guardians were, essentially, \Nautomatic-defense mechanisms.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.46,0:16:13.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That after death, those who \Noffer themselves to be Guardians
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.62,0:16:15.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,are removed from the cycle of death and rebirth,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.88,0:16:18.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,becoming tools that safeguard human history.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.18,0:16:23.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it would still be worth it \Nif I could save someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.18,0:16:25.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,one person who was in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.17,0:16:27.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it's nothing like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.27,0:16:28.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.17,0:16:30.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you get lost in the \Nafterlife, you crappy priest!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.51,0:16:33.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even Hell wouldn't want anything to do with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.59,0:16:37.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Purgatory would call you a bad influence\Nand pass you off somewhere else!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.55,0:16:39.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And you aren't suited to Heaven,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.32,0:16:43.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so a eunuch like you should tangle himself \Nin a bed of thorns outside the gates!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.10,0:16:51.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Kotomine, you know that Tohsaka's \Nbeen given to me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.71,0:16:54.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the only one who has business with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.38,0:16:56.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, I have business with her, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.11,0:17:01.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You see, I require her to become the Holy Grail.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.12,0:17:07.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Once Archer and Saber are gone, \Nthe time will finally be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.68,0:17:11.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I do not want her to lose her freshness \Nthrough unnecessary fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.69,0:17:14.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let us get this over with quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.90,0:17:18.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lancer, dispose of that trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.15,0:17:20.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The vessel has no need of a heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.92,0:17:23.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Guardians don't save humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.70,0:17:26.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Guardians simply clean up the messes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.32,0:17:28.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They're beings that use their power
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.49,0:17:31.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to negate events that have already transpired,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.16,0:17:34.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,disasters of humanity's own making.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.22,0:17:38.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They're butchers that kill anyone who \Nthreatens the human world,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.55,0:17:41.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,without distinguishing good and evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.20,0:17:44.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What a joke...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.33,0:17:47.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How is that any different than \Nwhen I was powerless?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.41,0:17:49.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To save as many lives as possible...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.63,0:17:56.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying that you were unable \Nto fulfill that wish even once?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.71,0:17:58.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.05,0:18:03.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've culled the very people I wanted to save.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.90,0:18:07.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because of the stupid ideal of \Nbecoming a hero of justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.02,0:18:10.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sick of cleaning up after humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.22,0:18:15.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But as a Heroic Spirit, I'm doomed \Nto repeat that for all eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.31,0:18:17.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I'd never existed...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.49,0:18:20.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I could disappear, that might...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.62,0:18:24.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you kill a human destined to be a hero,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.22,0:18:27.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you think that that hero will never be born?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.79,0:18:33.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've waited for that opportunity, \Nhoping the day would come.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.63,0:18:35.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It will not work.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.42,0:18:38.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You already exist as a Guardian.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.80,0:18:41.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are outside the confines of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.01,0:18:46.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you eliminate this Shirou, \Nyou will not disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.91,0:18:48.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.45,0:18:51.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it isn't beyond the realm of possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.99,0:18:56.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I destroy not only his flesh, but also his spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.77,0:18:58.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,at the very least,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.38,0:19:02.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the mistake that is the hero of justice \Nwill not appear in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.45,0:19:05.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, Emiya Shirou?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.30,0:19:07.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I'm so unacceptable to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.32,0:19:09.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,kill yourself right here and end it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.59,0:19:16.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shirou!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.04,0:19:19.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, Lancer?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.85,0:19:21.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your target is a little girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.07,0:19:24.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Killing her should be simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.47,0:19:27.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.24,0:19:28.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't obey you this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.47,0:19:30.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.31,0:19:33.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to make me do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.28,0:19:35.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you'll have to use a Command Seal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.90,0:19:40.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You leave me no choice, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.92,0:19:46.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I order you by Command Seal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.00,0:19:51.25,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Emiya-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.25,0:19:53.54,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm leaving this fight before you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.66,0:19:57.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Kill yourself, Lancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.36,0:20:17.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lancer!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.02,0:20:24.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer, do you have regrets?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.05,0:20:26.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.53,0:20:33.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then I guess we're two different people, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.92,0:20:35.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.54,0:20:41.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what happens to me, \NI'll never regret a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.64,0:20:44.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And that's why I'll never accept you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.38,0:20:48.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you're my ideal,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.03,0:20:51.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then I'll just have to get rid of \Nthat mistaken ideal myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.51,0:20:55.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That way of thinking is where all of this started.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.70,0:20:59.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,One day, you will reach the \Npoint where you become me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.23,0:21:00.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.39,0:21:02.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That day will never come.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.57,0:21:04.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.17,0:21:05.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose it won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.29,0:21:10.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you won't run from here, in any event, \Nyou have no future.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.75,0:21:16.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.67,0:21:18.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay, Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.73,0:21:20.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.54,0:21:22.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I'd like for you to stand back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.21,0:21:28.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is a fight I need to have.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.88,0:21:30.72,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Trace...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.05,0:21:32.90,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.94,0:21:41.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Can you keep up with my blade works?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.99,0:21:46.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If your precision is even slightly off, \Nit will spell your death.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.67,0:23:27.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will take your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.89,0:23:30.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Once useless, always useless, I suppose...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.65,0:23:34.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I admired his wish to save someone \Nbecause it was beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.44,0:23:39.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't {\i1}want{\i0} to become one... \NI'm {\i1}going{\i0} to become one!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.60,0:23:40.05,Next,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(483,1)}Next Time \NUnlimited Blade Works.
